quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  7,74,"“And remember how He made you successors after Aad, and settled you in the land. You make for yourselves mansions on its plains, and carve out dwellings in the mountains. So remember God’s benefits, and do not roam the earth corruptingly.”"
  7,75,"The elite of his people, who were arrogant, said to the common people who had believed, “Do you know that Saleh is sent from his Lord?” They said, “We are believers in what he was sent with.”"
  7,76,"Those who were arrogant said, “We reject what you believe in.”"
  7,77,"So they hamstrung the she-camel, and defied the command of their Lord, and said, “O Saleh, bring upon us what you threaten us with, if you are one of the messengers.”"
  7,78,"Whereupon the quake overtook them, and they became lifeless bodies in their homes"
  7,79,"Then he turned away from them, and said, “O my people, I have delivered to you the message of my Lord, and I have advised you, but you do not like those who give advice.”"
  7,80,"And Lot, when he said to his people, “Do you commit lewdness no people anywhere have ever committed before you?”"
  7,81,“You lust after men rather than women. You are an excessive people.”